definitions: describing love or feelings that are not returned or reciprocated by the person they are directed toward
examples: His unrequited love for her lasted through college years
She wrote poetry about unrequited feelings in her diary

definitions: without any doubt, limitation or holding back in expression or commitment
not kept for a particular person or purpose in advance
examples: She gave her unreserved support to the new policy
The team received unreserved praise from management
Only unreserved seats remained available for the concert
The restaurant had several unreserved tables for walk-ins

definitions: describing a problem, question, or dispute that has not been answered or settled conclusively
examples: The unresolved conflict between neighbors continued for years
Several unresolved issues remained after the meeting ended

definitions: showing no reaction to something or failing to respond when expected to do so
examples: The patient remained unresponsive despite medical treatment attempts
Customer service was unresponsive to our repeated complaints

definitions: not held back by rules, self-control, or physical barriers in behavior or expression
examples: The children showed unrestrained joy at the surprise party
His unrestrained criticism offended several committee members present

definitions: not limited by rules, regulations, or conditions allowing complete freedom of action
examples: The pass gave unrestricted access to all building areas
She enjoyed unrestricted internet use at the library

definitions: describing fruit or crops that have not reached full maturity for eating
examples: The unripe bananas were still green and hard
Eating unripe tomatoes can cause stomach upset problems

definitions: better than all others with no one able to equal or surpass in quality
examples: Her unrivaled expertise made her the top consultant
The restaurant offers unrivaled views of the ocean

definitions: disorderly and disruptive, not responding to discipline or control attempts
examples: The teacher struggled with several unruly students daily
Her unruly hair refused to stay in place

definitions: not safe from danger, harm, or risk to health or security
examples: The old bridge was declared unsafe for vehicles
Walking alone at night felt unsafe in that neighborhood

definitions: lacking official permission, authorization, or approval from proper authorities
examples: The unsanctioned protest was broken up by police
Students held an unsanctioned party after the game

definitions: not clean or healthy, likely to cause disease through lack of cleanliness
examples: The restaurant was closed due to unsanitary kitchen conditions
Unsanitary water sources spread disease in the village

definitions: not meeting requirements or expectations, inadequate in quality or performance
examples: His unsatisfactory performance led to a warning letter
The hotel room was in unsatisfactory condition upon arrival

definitions: feeling that something is inadequate or wanting more than what was received
examples: Customers left unsatisfied with the poor service quality
She remained unsatisfied despite achieving her career goals

definitions: failing to give satisfaction or meet expectations leaving one wanting more
examples: The movie had an unsatisfying ending that disappointed viewers
He found the meal unsatisfying and still felt hungry

definitions: unpleasant to taste, smell, or think about in any way
involving dishonest or morally questionable behavior that causes disapproval
examples: The unsavory smell came from the garbage bins outside
The restaurant served an unsavory combination of flavors
He had an unsavory reputation in the business community
Police investigated her unsavory connections to criminal organizations

definitions: emerging from a dangerous or difficult situation without suffering any injury or damage
examples: She walked away unscathed from the car accident
The building survived the earthquake unscathed and structurally sound

definitions: happening without being planned or included in a schedule or timetable
examples: The plane made an unscheduled stop due to weather
An unscheduled meeting interrupted our afternoon work plans

definitions: not based on or using scientific methods, principles, or rigorous systematic approach
examples: His unscientific approach relied on guesswork and assumptions
The study was criticized for unscientific data collection methods

definitions: spoken or performed without a prepared script allowing for spontaneous expression
examples: The actor's unscripted comments surprised the talk show host
They preferred unscripted conversations to formal prepared speeches

definitions: willing to act dishonestly or unfairly to achieve goals without moral principles
examples: The unscrupulous businessman cheated his partners repeatedly
Unscrupulous lenders took advantage of desperate borrowers

definitions: having been opened or not closed with a seal or fastening
examples: The unsealed envelope had already been read by someone
Water leaked through the unsealed window during heavy rain

definitions: lacking security measures, collateral, or protection from unauthorized access or loss
not fastened, tied down, or held firmly in place
examples: The unsecured loan had a higher interest rate
Hackers accessed the unsecured wireless network easily
The unsecured cargo shifted dangerously during transport
An unsecured ladder fell and injured a worker

definitions: not seen or observed by anyone, remaining hidden from view or attention
examples: An unseen force seemed to move objects around
The problem went unseen until the inspection revealed it

definitions: willing to put other people's needs and wishes before one's own interests
examples: Her unselfish dedication to charity inspired many volunteers
The player made an unselfish pass to help teammates score

definitions: not yet resolved, decided, or agreed upon definitively
feeling anxious, worried, or disturbed about something
likely to change frequently, especially regarding weather conditions
examples: Several unsettled disputes remained between the two countries
The unsettled lawsuit continued through multiple court sessions
She felt unsettled after hearing the disturbing news
The strange noises left everyone feeling deeply unsettled
The unsettled weather brought rain and sunshine alternately
Markets remained unsettled due to economic uncertainty

definitions: unpleasant or ugly to see, causing visual displeasure or aesthetic offense
examples: The unsightly garbage pile ruined the neighborhood's appearance
She covered the unsightly scar with makeup every day

definitions: not having a signature where one is normally required or expected
not having signed a contract, especially in sports or entertainment
examples: The unsigned check could not be cashed at the bank
Several unsigned documents delayed the closing process
The talented unsigned artist performed at local venues
Three unsigned players attended the team's training camp

definitions: not having or requiring special skill or training for work or tasks
examples: Unskilled workers earned minimum wage at the factory
The job required only unskilled labor for basic assembly

definitions: remaining available for sale because no one has bought it yet
examples: Unsold inventory piled up in the warehouse storage area
The artist kept her unsold paintings in the studio

definitions: given or offered without being requested or asked for by the recipient
examples: She received unsolicited advice from well-meaning relatives constantly
The company sent unsolicited emails to thousands of addresses

definitions: remaining without a solution or answer, especially regarding mysteries or problems
examples: The unsolved murder case haunted detectives for decades
Several unsolved math problems challenge brilliant minds worldwide

definitions: lacking worldly experience, refinement, or complexity in manner or taste
not complicated or advanced in design, technology, or construction
examples: His unsophisticated palate preferred simple home cooking
The tourists seemed unsophisticated about local customs
The device used unsophisticated technology from earlier decades
Their unsophisticated approach actually solved the complex problem

definitions: in poor condition, likely to collapse or fail structurally
not based on valid reasoning or good judgment in thinking
examples: The inspector declared the old building structurally unsound
The unsound bridge was closed to all traffic
His unsound financial advice led to major losses
The theory rested on unsound scientific principles

definitions: too terrible, shocking, or bad to be expressed in words
examples: The refugees endured unspeakable horrors during the war
She witnessed unspeakable cruelty at the detention center

definitions: not stated clearly or exactly, left vague or undefined in detail
examples: The contract mentioned unspecified damages for breach violations
He left for an unspecified period of time

definitions: ordinary and not particularly impressive, exciting, or worthy of special attention
examples: The team delivered an unspectacular but solid performance
Sales showed unspectacular growth throughout the quarter period

definitions: not harmed, damaged, or negatively affected maintaining natural or original state
examples: The island remained unspoiled by tourism or development
Her unspoiled enthusiasm made teaching worthwhile every day

definitions: understood or implied without being stated openly in words or speech
examples: An unspoken agreement existed between the old friends
Their unspoken attraction was obvious to everyone watching

definitions: behaving unfairly or showing poor conduct contrary to the spirit of good sportsmanship
examples: The player received a penalty for unsportsmanlike conduct
His unsportsmanlike behavior embarrassed his teammates and coach

definitions: likely to change, fail, or give way suddenly without warning
prone to sudden changes in mood or mental state unpredictably
examples: The unstable economy worried investors and business owners
The unstable chemical compound required careful handling
His unstable behavior concerned his family and friends
She felt emotionally unstable after the traumatic experience

definitions: not held firmly in position, moving or likely to move from side to side
examples: Her unsteady hands made writing difficult after the accident
He walked with unsteady steps after the long illness

definitions: unable to be stopped or prevented from continuing or succeeding
examples: The team seemed unstoppable after winning ten straight games
Her unstoppable determination led to remarkable business success

definitions: without formal organization or systematic arrangement in form or approach
examples: The unstructured interview allowed for natural conversation flow
Children enjoyed unstructured play time during summer camp

definitions: not supported or proven by evidence, facts, or reliable testimony
examples: The newspaper retracted the unsubstantiated claims about corruption
Police dismissed the unsubstantiated rumors as mere gossip

definitions: failing to achieve the desired aim, goal, or intended successful outcome
examples: His unsuccessful attempts at business left him deeply discouraged
The unsuccessful surgery required a second corrective procedure

definitions: not fitting or appropriate for a particular purpose, person, or occasion
examples: The formal dress was unsuitable for the beach party
His aggressive personality made him unsuitable for customer service

definitions: not right or appropriate for something, lacking necessary qualities or compatibility
examples: They were completely unsuited for each other romantically
His skills were unsuited to the technical job requirements

definitions: not celebrated or praised publicly despite deserving recognition for achievements
examples: The unsung heroes of the pandemic were healthcare workers
She remained an unsung contributor to the project's success

definitions: not watched over or directed by someone in authority or with responsibility
examples: Children should not be left unsupervised near water
The unsupervised workers made several costly mistakes yesterday
